import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    ax = sns.lineplot(x='year', y='wheat', data=data)
    ax.set(xlabel='Year', ylabel='Wheat Production')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the trend in wheat production over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    ax = sns.lineplot(x='year', y='wheat', data=data, label='Wheat')
    ax2 = ax.twinx()
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='wages', data=data, ax=ax2, color='r', label='Wages')
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the average wheat production and wages over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
